column5: Hi there. Was just talking to Melinda. My background is just the same as it was, but I'm not the leader of the Younglings. They reject my leadership upon my return to Tar Valon. So I come back to Caemlyn immediately. I figure I arrived just recently, so maybe you could do a rumor? Or do I need to talk to Bethany? Either way, thanks.
hi, I believe I am heading to Tar Valon with you, Garen, Adia and your warder....just saying hi!

Sarei was born in the Borderlands, as an orphan he grew, sent to Caemlyn by his father. His father and mother died together. His father had been the warder and his mother an Aessedai. He dreamed to follow in his fathers footsteps. A dream hard come by. When he was young, he learned the way of the sword from merchants guards; the orphanary couldnt get his mind elsewhere though. He would challenge his friends and those who would try, to duel him. He only learned from his losses. He ran away a few times with his friends, to have an adventure, but always came back in the end. When he finally achieved manhood at seventeen, he left the orphanary for good.
**In a letter delivered to the Caemlyn palace by courier, on fine rich
